Publisher: Published by Giovanni Domenico de Rossi (Italian, 1619–1653)
Medium: Etching with some engraving, undescribed state.
Dimensions: Plate 21 3/16 x 16 1/16 in. (53.8 x 40.8 cm) [partly within plate margins due to cropping]
Description: Part of the top half of the map of Rome. Depicted is a southern part of the city with the Baths of Caracalla (referred to as Thermae Antoninianae), the Santa Sabina and part of the Tiber.
